{# Per-state STATUS GLYPH indicator (primer). A state-specific status icon —
   housing + breathing core (passing) / spinner arc (building) / disc + cross
   (critical) / disc + bang (warning) / dim core (offline) — that the generic
   circle/square/diamond shapes can't express. This is a first-class, all-genome
   slot capability: any paradigm declaring badge.indicator_shape="status-glyph"
   gets it. Geometry is resolver-supplied (status_glyph dict); the rendered icon
   is selected by the normalized status_glyph_state via slug interpolation — no
   state string compare here. The group is translated to the layout-computed
   indicator center so the icon shares the badge's reading line; partials draw
   around the local origin (0,0). #}
<g data-hw-zone="status" transform="translate({{ indicator_center_x }},{{ indicator_center_y }})">
{% include "frames/badge/indicators/status-glyph/" ~ (status_glyph_state | default('passing')) ~ ".j2" %}
</g>
